cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

This paper discusses regularization and optimization strategies in deep convolutional neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks such as image classification and object detection. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the mathematical formulation of these strategies, indicating a focus on the theoretical aspects of deep learning, which suggests that it could also be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance and computational cost of these strategies, which could also place it under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper's focus on improving the generalization of ConvNets could also place it under cs.CL (Computation and Language).
